    <p>The objective of sudoku is to enter a digit from 1 through 9 in each cell, in such a way that:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Each horizontal row contains each digit exactly once</li>
      <li>Each vertical column contains each digit exactly once</li>
      <li>Each subgrid or region contains each digit exactly once</li>
    </ol>
    <p>This explains the name of the game; in Japanese, sudoku means something like "numbers singly".</p>

    <p>Solving a sudoku puzzle does not require knowledge of mathematics; simple logic suffices. (Instead of digits, other symbols can be used, e.g. letters, as long as there are nine different symbols.)</p>

    <p>In each sudoku puzzle, several digits have already been entered (the "givens"); these may not be changed.</p>

    <p>The puzzler's job is to fill the remainder of the grid with digits â€“respecting, of course, the three constraints mentioned earlier.</p>
